<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">&quot;Serena and her big sister Venus Williams brought to mind Zora Neale Hurston&apos;s &apos;I feel most colored when I am thrown against a sharp white background.<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">"Serena and her big sister Venus Williams brought to mind Zora Neale Hurston's 'I feel most colored when I am thrown against a sharp white background.' This appropriated line, stenciled on canvas by Glenn Ligon, who used plastic letter stencils, smudging oil sticks, and graphite to transform the words into abstractions, seemed to be ad copy for some aspect of life for all black bodies" (p. 25).<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
