<div id="review_2684197952" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2684197952" />
    <a title="Trudie" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4617856-trudie"><img alt="Trudie" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1609152063p2/4617856.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2684197952?book_show_action=true">Oct 11, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Trudie" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Trudie" href="/user/show/4617856-trudie">Trudie</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4617856-trudie?shelf=read-harder-2019">read-harder-2019</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4617856-trudie?shelf=poetry">poetry</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2684197952" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1939594931009118796">I think this is probably excellent and I enjoyed most of it but my caveat needs to be I am inept at appreciating poetry. I nearly always would rather spend time with a novel. I can only point feebly at bits I liked without having the language to say why. Predictably, my finger hovers over sections that are more like prose than poetry ( that bit on Serena was a highlight). <br/>Thus, I must nod in deference to other reviewers for explaining what makes this one such an acclaimed poetry collection, for </span>
  <span id="freeText1939594931009118796" style="display:none">I think this is probably excellent and I enjoyed most of it but my caveat needs to be I am inept at appreciating poetry. I nearly always would rather spend time with a novel. I can only point feebly at bits I liked without having the language to say why. Predictably, my finger hovers over sections that are more like prose than poetry ( that bit on Serena was a highlight). <br />Thus, I must nod in deference to other reviewers for explaining what makes this one such an acclaimed poetry collection, for my own part I thought, yeah, this has given me some "gut-punch" moments and thats all I can ask of my poetry.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1939594931009118796" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
